# NgChat Backend

Node.js + Express + WebSocket backend for the NgChat Angular application.

## Stack

- **Express** — REST API
- **ws** — WebSocket server
- **bcryptjs** — password hashing
- **jsonwebtoken** — JWT auth
- **TypeScript** throughout
- **In-memory store** (no database needed to run)

## Quick Start

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Server starts on `http://localhost:3000`.

## REST Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | ✗ | Register new user |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | ✗ | Login, receive JWT |
| GET | `/api/channels` | ✓ | List all channels |
| GET | `/api/channels/:id/messages` | ✓ | Last 50 messages |
| POST | `/api/channels` | ✓ | Create a channel |
| GET | `/health` | ✗ | Health check |

## WebSocket

Connect to `ws://localhost:3000?token=<JWT>`.

### Events you send (client → server)
```json
{ "type": "message:new", "payload": { "channelId": "ch-general", "content": "Hello!" } }
{ "type": "message:edit", "payload": { "messageId": "...", "content": "Edited text" } }
{ "type": "message:delete", "payload": { "messageId": "..." } }
```

### Events you receive (server → client)
```json
{ "type": "message:new", "payload": { /* Message object */ } }
{ "type": "message:edit", "payload": { /* Message object */ } }
{ "type": "message:delete", "payload": { "id": "..." } }
{ "type": "user:status", "payload": { "userId": "...", "status": "online|offline" } }
```

## Seed Data

On startup the server seeds three channels: `#general`, `#random`, `#angular`.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `PORT` | `3000` | HTTP/WS port |
| `JWT_SECRET` | `ng-chat-dev-secret-change-in-prod` | JWT signing secret |
| `FRONTEND_ORIGIN` | `http://localhost:4200` | CORS allowed origin |

For production, create a `.env` file:
```
PORT=3000
JWT_SECRET=your-strong-secret-here
FRONTEND_ORIGIN=https://your-frontend-domain.com
```

## Running Both Frontend + Backend

```bash
# Terminal 1 — backend
cd ng-chat-backend
npm install && npm run dev

# Terminal 2 — frontend
cd ng-chat
npm install && ng serve
```

Open http://localhost:4200, register an account, and start chatting.
